Greek Opposition Leader Says Not Interested in Unity Government

-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s   a n d   E l e n i   C h r e p a
-- 
2011-10-10T13:25:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/greek-opposition-leader-says-not-interested-in-unity-government.html
Antonis Samaras, the leader of
 Greece ’s biggest opposition party, said he wasn’t interested in
teaming up with Prime Minister  George Papandreou  in a national
unity government.  “Unity government scenarios don’t interest us,” Samaras,
who heads the New Democracy party, said in statements televised
live on state-run NET TV.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  